about.summary: bsc is a high performance file compressor based on lossless, block-sorting data compression algorithms.

name: libbsc
raw_meta_yaml:
# Note: there are many handy hints in comments in this example -- remove them when you've finalized your recipe

{% set name = "libbsc" %}
{% set version = "3.1.1.a0" %}

package:
  name: {{ name|lower }}
  version: {{ version }}

source:
  url: https://github.com/IlyaGrebnov/libbsc/archive/3dea3471251fbac72c895f42f22a1aa75b81da33.tar.gz
  sha256: a7be8d2d9a4188b4f99e5d5c10ea744a88599dca2ec9b14118f61e6313c64a1a

build:
  number: 0
  skip: True  # [win]

requirements:
  build:
    - {{ compiler('cxx') }}
    - llvm-openmp  # [osx]
    - libgomp      # [linux]
    - make
  host:
  run:

test:
  commands:
      - bsc -h

about:
  home: https://github.com/IlyaGrebnov/libbsc
  license: Apache-2.0
  license_family: APACHE
  license_file: LICENSE
  summary: 'bsc is a high performance file compressor based on lossless, block-sorting data compression algorithms.'

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    # GitHub IDs for maintainers of the recipe.
    - ShubhamChandak94
